s  People come to Jane Addams for the excellent education in social work and social justice. But, the student experience at Jane Addams also includes a variety of events and other opportunities for learning, socializing and affirming your passion for social justice.      A Glimpse Into Life at Jane Addams       Go to slide 1    Go to slide 2    Go to slide 3    Go to slide 4    Go to slide 5    Go to slide 6    Go to slide 7    Go to slide 8    Go to slide 9    Go to slide 10    Go to slide 11    Go to slide 12    Go to slide 13    Go to slide 14    Go to slide 15    Go to slide 16    Go to slide 17    Go to slide 18    Go to slide 19                Go to the next slide    Go to the previous slide       MSW students mixing, meeting and enjoying refreshments at the annual New Student Orientation and Reception.              Go to the next slide    Go to the previous slide       A class in our School Social Work specialization, being taught by Clinical Assistant Professor Annette Johnson.              Go to the next slide    Go to the previous slide       The courtyard outside the building provides a public open space with the Chicago skyline in the background.              Go to the next slide    Go to the previous slide       Scholarship recipients, alumni, donors and faculty enjoy each other's company at the annual Dean's Scholarship Reception.              Go to the next slide    Go to the previous slide       PhD students and alumni of the PhD program come together every year at the Doctoral Student and PhD Alumni Reception.              Go to the next slide    Go to the previous slide       Jane Addams Student Government organizes events such as Jane's Spotlights, highlighting the research of Jane Addams faculty.              Go to the next slide    Go to the previous slide       PhD students in the Analysis of Social Work Practice Approaches class visiting the Jane Addams Hull-House Museum to gain an understanding of historical roots of the settlement house move